Brown College offers a work study program for students, allowing them to find part-time employment on campus. Students can also seek part-time employment through Career Services. The contact information for admissions, campus tours, and liaison officers are as follows:

Admissions: 416-415-5000 ext. 4805, tours@georgebrown.ca
Liaison Officers: Liz Henriques (ext. 2929, lhenriques@georgebrown.ca), Robyn Papoff (ext. 2267, rpapoff@georgebrown.ca)
Mailing Address: P.O. Box 1015, Station B, Toronto, ON M5T 2T9
Campus Locations: Available on the Campus Tours website or by contacting tours@georgebrown.ca

Excludes upgrading and preparatory programs. For more information, contact the Enrolment Planning and Reporting Department at George Brown College or visit their website. The information contained in the website is subject to change without notice.

Key Performance Indicators: Ministry of Training, Colleges and Universities (September 25, 2019)
George Brown College Foundation

Learn more about George Brown College's land acknowledgment and sign up for updates on application deadlines, college news, upcoming events, tours, and more by visiting their website or contacting ask.george@georgebrown.ca (416-415-2000). TTY: 1-877-515-5559. Visit George Brown College's Social Media Hub for more information.
